# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your Python version with the community or team.
#   For an application or device, it should be shared so that the environment matches.
#   Uncomment one:
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, they may get conflicts.
#   Uncomment one:
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock contains exact versions, but may be OS-specific.
#   Uncomment one:
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock contains exact versions.
#   Uncomment one:
#pdm.lock

# virtualenv
.venv
venv/
ENV/
env/

